output.content: Agentic workflow editors represent a new paradigm in automation where AI agents can intelligently navigate, modify, and execute complex multi-step processes with minimal human intervention. Unlike traditional workflow tools that require explicit rule definitions, these editors leverage large language models to understand context, make decisions, and adapt workflows dynamically based on real-time conditions and outcomes. They enable non-technical users to orchestrate sophisticated automation pipelines through natural language instructions, while providing developers with powerful abstractions for building self-improving systems that learn from execution patterns.
